musicTracks.title: Bourbon at Dawn
musicTracks.feedDescription:
Good times, great vibes. "Bourbon at Dawn" is a summer jam that kicks off the party and keeps it going. Inspired by double entendre cocktail names and paying homage to some of America's favorite bar songs, this tune is good humored, witty, and carefree. Capturing the energy of a fun night out, the country rock instrumentation gives this hi-res studio production a warm, live performance feel

Written and Performed by Sara Jade
Produced, mixed and master by John Kennedy

musicTracks.title: Jacoma
musicTracks.feedDescription:
Nashville produced Americana ballad with traditional country instrumentation, powerful vocal performance and well woven poetry. "Jacoma" (hard "J") earned the artist a place in the International Songwriting Competition Semifinals for the Americana category and a San Diego Music Award nomination.
Written and Performed by Sara Jade
Produced by John Kennedy

musicTracks.title: Wait Destiny
musicTracks.feedDescription:
Destiny waits for no man, but will it wait for Sara Jade? The answers can come in mysterious ways... Like when you are at a crosswalk in Madrid, Spain, thinking about your dreams, and you misread a Walt Disney logo as "Wait Destiny"! A trick of the mind? Or a message? Whatever the case, inspiration struck Sara Jade!

"Wait Destiny" is an elevating Nu Disco track enriched with funk bass, transcendent soundscapes and dance appeal. Reimagined from it's 2020 debut on YouTube, Sara Jade has turned up the rhythmic heat with heavy hitting dance drums and is hailing the mothership with rich choral harmonies. Cleverly layered instrumentation gives the listener plenty of melodic ear candy to sink their teeth into on replay so that each listen feels fresh.

musicTracks.title: All Apology
musicTracks.feedDescription:
Meditative and moody like a cup of coffee on a rainy day, "All Apology" is a stripped down piano vocal track with acoustic intimacy. Reflective lyrics balanced with warm instrumental and vocal delivery
Written and performed by Sara Jade
Mixing and Mastering Engineer François Michaud of Wild Horse Studio

musicTracks.title: Swallow Me Whole
musicTracks.feedDescription:
Acoustic chill with a poetic intrigue. "Swallow Me Whole" is inspired by artists like Hozier and Damien Rice, blending comforting finger-picked guitar rhythms with contemporary melodies and intimate vocal delivery. Written and Performed by Sara Jade and Matt Kreuder
Mixing and Mastering by François Michaud of Wild Horse Studio

musicTracks.title: Lady Neptune
musicTracks.description:
From the album 'deathdreams'
Written by Emily Whitehurst
Performed by Survival Guide
Produced, recorded, and mixed by Bob Hoag at Flying Blanket Recording
Mastered by Jason Livermore at The Blasting Room

LYRICS:

She comes between us
But we can’t see it
Scratching with pins and needles
Saying the perfect words
Up overhead the vultures circle
We’re still a bit too fresh but
They won’t be waiting long

I can save us all if I die before I wake
Pray it’s not all a mistake as I go under
Soak me to the bone
No one showed me how...

musicTracks.title: What We Are
musicTracks.description:
What We Are
Ben Doerfel, Ed Doerfel,
We were fuel on fire
we were Bullets from a gun
We were rising higher 
Getting further from the sun
We were midnight riders 
Like the lightning in the dark
Tho the moon shined brighter
They called us shooting stars 
What we are
Isn't who we are 
What we are 
Was never who we are
You're an all night fighter 
I'm running out of breathe 
We're still chasing flames 
But there's ashes in our bed
Now I'm an empty bottle 
So I drink to pass the time 
You're lonely heartbreak
Who can't look...

We picked this song to release on Episode 4 of our podcast, "Into The Doerfel-verse" If you find any value in this song, please let us know!

musicTracks.title: Out of the Blue
musicTracks.description:
In 1993 I released my first CD, entitled "Peace Pieces" as part of a seven-year art/life performance.

"Out of the Blue" is where my music seems to come from, which I consider more a series of discoveries than compositions. I start with an idea and keep exploring it, paying attention to where it wants to go. Along the way I try to make it sound as I would like to hear it, and to stop before it gets spoiled.

Information on the process at http://willshare.com/v4v/album/PeacePieces
